OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1780974217
OL,3,CElectrician faces life sentence for
OL,4,Cmurdering judge's daughter in a rage
OL,6,FIn the aftermath of the killing, he
OL,7,Fadmitted "I lost it" and the trial
OL,8,Fheard how he had lost his temper when
OL,9,Fhe believed Ms Rook had told him a lie.
OL,11,FIn his defence, George insisted he did
OL,12,Fnot have a "short fuse", but friends
OL,13,Fand family of Ms Rook gave evidence of
OL,14,Fhis true character.
OL,16,FMs Rook's best friend, Sian Davin,
OL,17,Ftold jurors she believed George needed
OL,18,Ftherapy for his anger issues and
OL,19,Fdescribed an incident when he pushed
OL,20,FMs Rook against a wall and grabbed her
OL,21,Faround the throat.
OL,26,@oD@JOUoD@TO]tD@LOUtD@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
