PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1780974217
OL,3,CElectrician faces life sentence for
OL,4,Cmurdering judge's daughter in a rage
OL,6,F"She was a deeply caring and
OL,7,Fempathetic person who had set up a
OL,8,Fcharity working with women traumatised
OL,9,Fby domestic and sexual abuse.
OL,11,F"Clifton George sought to minimise his
OL,12,Factions by claiming he had lost
OL,13,Fcontrol.
OL,15,FHowever, the evidence demonstrated
OL,16,Fthat after assaulting Ms Rook, he
OL,17,Fretrieved a knife and returned to
OL,18,Fcontinue the attack, and the
OL,19,Fprosecution was able to prove the
OL,20,Fnecessary intent for murder.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
